                    <span>Not recommended, although some people like it a lot.Â  More errors in the text than others, making you go to the web for errata pages.  Relies too much on just presenting source code for the reader to type in, without adequate explanation of what the code does and why it's structured the way it is.  Less of a gentle introduction than Hillegass's book "Cocoa Programming for Mac OS X", less comprehensive than Anguish's book "Cocoa Programming".</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Try a different book first.</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>2</span>
